<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,1623,1938]" box="[151,558,1623,1650]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,1623,1650]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
4.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,1623,1938]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1659,1686]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe, largely lacking in the south and southeast (except for 
<collectingCountry box="[1095,1151,1659,1686]" name="Italy" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Italy</collectingCountry>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[1174,1273,1659,1685]" name="Portugal" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: one province (Trás-os-Montes e Alto Douro).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,1623,1938]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1732,1758]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Ecology.</emphasis>
The only sampling site of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[775,870,1731,1757]" name="Portugal" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Portugal</collectingCountry>
were permanent pastures (Lameiros) bordered by 
<taxonomicName box="[151,267,1768,1794]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Betula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[151,224,1768,1794]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Betula</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, and an ancient bog that was drained in the 20th century for cultivation. In northwestern Europe, this species is restricted to open oligotrophic biotopes where it can be found in numbers on flowers of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pollet 2000)" authorityName="Pollet" authorityYear="2000" baseAuthorityName="Pollet" baseAuthorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Potentilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erecta">
<emphasis box="[1250,1436,1804,1830]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Potentilla erecta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pollet, M." box="[159,294,1839,1866]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref34362" refString="Pollet, M. (2000) A documented Red List of the dolichopodid flies (Diptera: Dolichopodidae) of Flanders [in Dutch with English summary]. Communications of the Institute of Nature Conservation, 8, 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="2000">Pollet 2000</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,1623,1938]" box="[199,703,1875,1902]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1875,1902]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
1.1 (very rare). Fairly rare (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,1623,1938]" box="[199,452,1911,1938]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,1911,1938]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Activity period.</emphasis>
June.
</paragraph>
